# ðŸš€ TransmorphAI - AI-Powered Data Transformation for APIs  

## ðŸ“Œ Introduction  

**TransmorphAI** is a Python library designed to **simplify communication between APIs**. Normally, when integrating with an API, developers must strictly follow the APIâ€™s documentation, ensuring that their requests match the required data types and structure.  

With **TransmorphAI**, this is no longer necessary. API consumers can **send data in any format** (JSON, XML, plain text) without worrying about how the final API expects it.  

### **ðŸ”¹ Why Use TransmorphAI?**  
âœ… API consumers **donâ€™t need to adapt** to the API providerâ€™s documentation.  
âœ… You only need to know **the parameter names**, not their types or format.  
âœ… The API receiving the request, which has **TransmorphAI integrated**, will **automatically format and validate** the data before storing it.  
âœ… API consumers **donâ€™t need to know the final format**â€”they just send the data, and **TransmorphAI handles the transformation**.  

---

## ðŸ›  Features  
âœ… **Supports multiple input formats** (JSON, XML, plain text).  
âœ… **Automatically formats data** according to the APIâ€™s required structure.  
âœ… **Detects missing required fields** and alerts if any are missing.  
âœ… **Maintains correct data types** (e.g., converts numbers, strings, and lists correctly).  
âœ… **Detects input language** and preserves the intended output format.  
âœ… **Secure and flexible**, allowing easy integration into any Python-based API.  

